name: Navy Pier
directions: Family bathroom by woman's bathroom on navy pier building.

name: Sleepy's
directions: Near the back of the store
comment: Has multiple bathrooms, all single stall and all accessible - however you may want to browse a bit just so it's less awkward

name: Flatbread Company
directions: Go to the back of the restaurant and turn right. It's at the end of the hallway

name: Cafe DiCocoa's
directions: Behind the counter, through a curtained door on your right

name: Regal Cinema Barkley Village
directions: Right side of lobby as you enter the theater.
comment: Not clear if you have to be a customer or not.

name: Books@cafe
comment: You have to be a paying customer i.e buy a drink or water

name: BriarPatch Co-Op
directions: Front of the store to the left when you enter. Dropped pin on Refuge map may not be in exact spot--look for the big co-op grocery store!
comment: Awesome co-op offers full trans-inclusive benefits to employees!

name: Blaze Fast Fire'd Pizza
directions: Located at Fashion Island Mall. Upper floor.
comment: Must be a paying customer.

name: Panera bread - Phoenix Park
directions: In back left of restaurant.
comment: For paying customers. Locked with a code and has locks that display vacancy.

name: Elm City Games
directions: In the second room, to the left

name: Nate's Wings and Waffles
comment: Probably for paying customers but it's not locked. Up some stairs on the left.

name: The Alliance of People with Disabilities
directions: First floor, open Mon-Thu 9-12 and 1-4.
comment: Restrooms are for consumers of the Alliance or people coming in for information and referral. Any disability qualifies you to be a consumer (including mental health) and no one will check your disability card.

name: Rite Aid
directions: Back right corner of the store next to the pharmacy
comment: Single stall, always clean :)

name: Hornell junior high school
directions: In the junior high turn right from the main entrance and walk down to the vending machines. Then turn right again and walk to the end of the hall to the fitness suite. At the back of the room near the promethean board there is a single gender nuetral bathroom.
comment: The fitness suit is sometimes locked or there is a class going on but you can also use the nurse bathroom or the staff bathroom in the junior high

name: Hornell junior high school
directions: If you walk in the front door of either side of the school (senior or junior) go straight towards the rotunda and if your coming from the senior side go left and the opposite for the junior side. At the end of the hallway the nurses office has a single bathroom.
comment: If you speak to the dean or the principal you can ask to use the bathroom and they will most likely let you use them. Tell them you want to use it to make the other students and yourself more comfortable.

name: Hornell junior high school
directions: Second floor of junior high side
comment: Ask the principal or the dean to use it because it is a staff bathroom, but if they know your situation they will most likely allow you to use it. Tell them its to make the students and yourself feel more comfortable.

name: signal
directions: on the left

name: Ballard Market
directions: In the back, with the raw meat

name: Video Game Arcade
directions: Back of the video arcade
comment: Call ahead! They are only open by appointment, but the owner is LGBT friendly understands TG issues and will open for you if they are available. They are only 15 minutes off I-80.

name: Starbucks
directions: To the left from the counter.

name: 8780 W Charleston Blvd, Las Vegas, NV 89117, USA
directions: Starbucks, in the back
comment: one mens room, one womens room, both single and accessible

name: Dunkin Donuts
directions: Back right of the store

name: Lucia Ristorante
directions: In the back of the restaurant to the left of the kitchen and the far side of the bar.
comment: You have to buy their food or drink

name: Subway
directions: Walk in and turn slightly to your right, then straight forward, bathrooms are easily visible
comment: I ate here so I'm not aware if you have to be a paying customer... you could get a water or a bag of chips tho

name: Amc theatre
directions: A individual single stall family restroom located on either side of the theatre. Take a left or a right at the lobby and the bathrooms are located beside theatres 2 and 8 on the left side and theatres 9 and 15 on the right side.
comment: They typically want you to have a ticket, but if it's a busy weekend you can ask the greeter if you can use the restroom really fast. Then, depending on the greeted, you can go in if you come back after using the bathroom. As long as you come back within 10 minutes or so you shouldn't have any trouble.

name: Jimmy's Diner
directions: In back to the left
comment: You can usually get away with walking in to use it

name: The Cannery District
directions: On the right as you walk down the entrance hall

name: Caffe O-Le
directions: Bathroom on the left side of the restaurant is gender neutral single stall. 2 gendered single stall bathrooms on the right side of the restaurant.

name: Brush Creek Community Center and Pool
Chocolateria San Churro
directions: It's in the back of the restaurant past the counter
comment: Because of its location I'd say you'd have to ask or be a paying customer

name: Platform 3, Central Station
directions: In the first class lounge on platform 3, turn left when you go in.
comment: Ticket barriers into the station, but no checks to get into the 1st class lounge. Very rarely any staff in the lounge, just try not to look too out of place.

name: Mountain Loop Highway Country Store (AKA Shell gas station)
directions: No public restroom inside store. Port-a-potties around side of building, not gendered.

name: Target
directions: To the left immediately after entering the doors

name: Murphy Hall
directions: Take west elevator to 3rd floor, down hall to left-- room number 3124
comment: There is no men's gendered restroom on this floor, so many men in the offices use it.

name: Novi Public Library
directions: There is a family bathroom located on the ground floor in the children's section, back near where the big red racecar is.

name: Thompson Hall at University of Puget Sound
directions: Third floor. Not sure if there were elevators but there might be!
comment: It's in a campus building so there will be students around, but no cost!

name: Lemonade
directions: In the back to the left. One toilet in each room, all private.
comment: Should probably buy food first, but if you really have to go they are very nice people and will be okay if you ask them. Or if it is crowded just go ahead.

name: Aberdeen Square
directions: Located on the third floor in the food court. Single stall family bathroom next to the A&W.

name: Chocolati
directions: One parallel to the espresso machine and one in the far back

name: Creamistry
comment: It's an ice cream shop but you don't have to buy anything to use the restroom and you might have to ask for the key.

name: Creamistry
comment: It's an ice cream shop but you don't have to buy anything to use the restroom and you might have to ask for the key.

name: All Souls Pizza
directions: To the left of front entrance
comment: Door opens inside, tight space

name: Insomnia Cookies
directions: Slightly to the left and in the back.
comment: It's always polite to buy something from the establishment whose bathroom you are using - and their cookies are $1.59 apiece, so treat yo self! (Vegan + gf options available!)

name: Phong Lan
directions: Through the front door, to the back area, then turn right through an opeing in the wall NOT ALL THE WAY BACK THATS ATHE KITCHEN!!
comment: I'm fairly sure you have to be a paying customer, but the food here is great!

name: K Gas Station
directions: all the way to the back
comment: went in and didnt buy anything, had no issue. Condom dispenser in men's room, don't know about women's, but it's also single stall

name: Lowe's Home Improvement
directions: Up in the front by the customer service (facing the parking lot) to the left of the gendered restrooms.
comment: Marked "Unisex Restroom". Regular flush toilet. Has Koala baby changer in it (as does the mens). Air dryer for hands.

name: Sips Specialty Coffee House
directions: At the back of the shop, on the right

name: Sips Specialty Coffee House
directions: At the back of the shop, on the right side of the wall

name: Sips Specialty Coffee House
directions: At the back of the shop, on the right side of the wall

name: Cherry Republic
directions: At the far back right of the store
comment: There are two single-use "pit stops" clearly marked unisex and handicap accessible. They each have baby-changing tables and paper towel dispensers. Well-lit, reasonably clean given how busy the place is.

name: Tiki Hut
directions: across the wooden walk way, past tiki hut, on the side of the hotel building kind of. (follow the signs).

name: Maria Hall, Webster Groves, MO 63119, USA
comment: Students use and faculty

name: Race Way gas station
directions: walk into the gas station and turn left after you get past the cashier
comment: walked in without buying anything, had no issue

name: Venus Envy Ottawa
directions: Wheelchair accessible store (push activated door). Straight to back of the shop, last door on the right. Menstrual products under the sink.
comment: This is an education-based sex shop that serves many communities, including trans, Two-Spirit, and gender diverse people. It is open to all ages.

name: Japanese Garden Entrance at Hermann Park
directions: The Japanese Garden is located on the northwest side of Hermann Park, across from Whistletop Prairie, along Fannin Street. On the east side of the garden (closest to the Pioneer Memorial Obelisk and Reflecting Pool) is the entryway building, with a large stone and a lantern in front of it. Head through under the roof and take an immediate left behind the dividing fence, which obscures the entrance to the restrooms from the garden.
comment: Two gendered, single-stall locking bathrooms and a drinking fountain, and a bench nearby. Because it's in the Museum District it should be a pretty accepting area and safe place as well. They're not the nicest restrooms, because they're outside, but the door locks and it has a flush toilet and sink- as well as the divider for privacy from the rest of the garden.

name: Petco
street: Park Lakes Landing, 9603 North Sam Houston Parkway East
directions: From main entrance, head to the back-right of the store, you should see a passageway. Take the first left into a hallway with both gendered single-stall bathrooms.

name: Lowes
directions: front wall of store near the gendered restrooms
comment: unisex/family/handicap accessible stall

name: 28 Shelter Cove Ln, Hilton Head Island, SC 29928, USA
Cherokee Emergency Vet Clinic
directions: on the right near neurology

name: Plato's Closet
directions: To the left of the dressing area
comment: You have to ask an employee to unlock it

name: Moretti's
directions: There is a single stall gender neutral bathroom on the first floor back by the kitchen. If it's a busy night, you can probably just walk in and use the bathroom and leave without buying anything.

name: Dunkin Donuts
directions: When you walk in its on the right side of the Dunkin, after the counter.
comment: I've used it many times.

name: Ground floor
directions: Follow the signs to the toilets on the ground floor & faith room. There are two GN accessible toilets on the right

name: First floor
directions: Follow directions to the toilets, there are a number of GN accessible toilets near the gender separated area

name: St Martin's coffee
directions: Upstairs and straight ahead
comment: I think they'd like you to make a purchase but they are so lovely here

name: 341 Barrenjoey Rd, Newport NSW 2106, Australia
directions: Second floor, go to the right from the elevator

name: Couche-tard
directions: Just ask the cashier
comment: Free and clean :)

name: County Rd C, Andover, MN 55304, USA
directions: Near pavilion and Bunker Hills sphere structure playground

name: shelter restaurant
directions: to the left when you come in the front door, by the  pool table

name: Verizon Witeless
directions: In back of store thru grey unmarked door by desk.  Women's is single stall.  Didn't check men's.
comment: They ask what you are there for when you walk in.  Can just say browsing for new phone.

name: McDonald's
directions: When you go into the building, go to the right where the tables are, and walk to the back, door has a sign on it. Go through and there's two doors, both neutral, with toilet, bin, sink.
comment: Not sure if you have to be a paying customer, but no one really cares if you aren't.

name: University of Detroit Mercy School of Law
directions: All gender, accessible restroom on the first floor of the law school, across the hall from the Career Services Office
comment: closed campus

name: GoBerry
comment: sign says for guests only, but they're pretty flexible if you ask

name: Brueggers Bagels
directions: downstairs (not wheelchair accessible).
comment: sign says you have to be a paying customer but they're flexible about it

name: Hot numbers coffee
directions: At the back, opposite side of the divide to the counter.

name: Independence Mall
directions: The bathrooms are located in their own building right next to the Liberty Bell Center

name: Dock Street Brewery
directions: When you walk in the front door, go left, and then just go straight down the hall
comment: Pretty sure they're just for restaurant patrons

name: Super Target/Starbucks
directions: a single-stall family bathroom by the gendered bathrooms

name: Subway
directions: Near the back.
comment: Single stalls. They are gendered, but it's unlikely anyone will give you any trouble.

name: Sobeys
directions: Near the bakery and meat section.
comment: Anybody can use it. It's a unisex single stall for customers.

name: Sweet Dreams Teashop
directions: Near the counter.
comment: Super funky, queer-friendly, easily-accessible bubble tea place. You can play board games, work on your schoolwork, read a book. You can ask for the WiFi password if you buy something. Bathrooms are clean and gender-neutral.

name: Sister Louisa's Church of the Living Room and Ping Pong Emporium
directions: There are 3 (THREE!) whole gender neutral restrooms in this tiny bar! Two are straight to the back at the bottom of the staircase, and the other is upstairs at the very back by the darts.
comment: Good place to chill with your queer pals on Sunday nights when there's less straight people hanging around.
